# Database (Isar)

- Use **Isar** for local persistence; schemas live in `data/models/` or `core/database/`.
- Annotate models with `@collection`; run `scripts/gen.sh` after schema changes.
- Access Isar only from **datasources** in the data layer — never from UI or blocs.
- Wrap DB errors in domain-friendly `Failure` types from `lib/core/errors/`.
- Use migrations carefully; version collections when breaking schema changes occur.
- Close / dispose Isar instances via DI lifecycle, not in widgets.

```dart
// ✅ GOOD — datasource owns Isar access
class DashboardLocalDatasource {
  final Isar _isar;
  Future<List<DashboardModel>> getAll() => _isar.dashboardModels.where().findAll();
}
```
